    {
      "id": "5a93c517_41690dbd",
      "file_path": "kubernetes/aai/values.yaml",
      "patchset_number": 12,
      "line": 7,
      "message": "This is meant to be a temporary fix. I agree, assigning static ip isn't good, but we don't have choice.\nPolicy drools container is running with user policy, not root. I tried Yuri's solution, but it can't update /etc/hosts, Persmission Denied.\nThe IP I chose here is the last IP of the /16 used by k8s for cluser-ip, very very little chance it will be picked up.",
